{"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.ExtendDeriv","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.MeanValue"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.lean#L217-L222","name":"hasDerivAt_of_hasDerivAt_of_ne'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.html#hasDerivAt_of_hasDerivAt_of_ne'","doc":"If a real function `f` has a derivative `g` everywhere but at a point, and `f` and `g` are\ncontinuous at this point, then `g` is the derivative of `f` everywhere. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.lean#L183-L212","name":"hasDerivAt_of_hasDerivAt_of_ne","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.html#hasDerivAt_of_hasDerivAt_of_ne","doc":"If a real function `f` has a derivative `g` everywhere but at a point, and `f` and `g` are\ncontinuous at this point, then `g` is also the derivative of `f` at this point. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.lean#L148-L178","name":"has_deriv_at_interval_right_endpoint_of_tendsto_deriv","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.html#has_deriv_at_interval_right_endpoint_of_tendsto_deriv","doc":"If a function is differentiable on the left of a point `a : ℝ`, continuous at `a`, and\nits derivative also converges at `a`, then `f` is differentiable on the left at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.lean#L114-L143","name":"has_deriv_at_interval_left_endpoint_of_tendsto_deriv","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.html#has_deriv_at_interval_left_endpoint_of_tendsto_deriv","doc":"If a function is differentiable on the right of a point `a : ℝ`, continuous at `a`, and\nits derivative also converges at `a`, then `f` is differentiable on the right at `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.lean#L40-L109","name":"has_fderiv_at_boundary_of_tendsto_fderiv","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ExtendDeriv.html#has_fderiv_at_boundary_of_tendsto_fderiv","doc":"If a function `f` is differentiable in a convex open set and continuous on its closure, and its\nderivative converges to a limit `f'` at a point on the boundary, then `f` is differentiable there\nwith derivative `f'`. "}]}